"O, my kids, my kids!
The wolf has eaten my kids!"
"I am here," cried the kid in the
clock.
"Where, where, where?" cried
Mother Goat.
"Here, mother, in the clock. "
The mother ran to the clock door.
Out jumped the kid.
"Where are the other kids?" said
the Mother Goat.
"The wolf ate them, " said the kid.
"He ate all but me.
I hid in the clock."

